properties.areaDesc: San Luis Obispo County Central Coast; Santa Barbara County Central Coast
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 3 at 2:19AM PST until January 3 at 11:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 8 to 12 feet through this
morning, and will gradually subside in the afternoon. Dangerous
rip currents are expected.

* WHERE...West facing beaches of the San Luis Obispo and Santa
Barbara County Central Coast.

* WHEN...Until 11 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...There is an increased risk for ocean drowning. Rip
currents can pull swimmers and surfers out to sea. Large
breaking waves can cause injury, wash people off beaches and
rocks, and capsize small boats near shore.
properties.instruction:
Remain out of the water due to dangerous surf conditions, or stay
near occupied lifeguard towers. Rock jetties can be deadly in
such conditions, stay off the rocks.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM PST THIS MORNING
